Colombia Stocks: Bancolombia, Helm Bank, Textiles Fabricato

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-04-01T20:12:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/colombia-stocks-bancolombia-helm-bank-textiles-fabricato.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.7 percent to 14,364.27, while the
Colcap Index declined 0.6 percent to 1,708.59.  Banks rose after  Colombia ’s policy makers said they may
need to raise  interest rates  less than in previous economic
cycles, according to minutes of the board’s March 18 meeting.  Bancolombia SA (BCOLO)  , the nation’s biggest lender,
advanced 2.1 percent to 29,720 pesos.  Helm Bank SA (PFBHELMB)  , the Colombian lender formerly
known as Banco de Credito, gained 2.1 percent to 390 pesos.  Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)  , the Medellin-
based textile producer and exporter, increased 1.4 percent to
42.5 pesos. Colombian President  Juan Manuel Santos  said he’d
take additional measures to curb gains in the peso if necessary
to offset pressure on the currency from international
investment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
